{"lemma":"خُمْس","slug":"خُمْس","root":"خمس","root_slug":"خمس","root_link":"/words/roots/خمس","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خُمْس","root":"خمس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","num"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11499","n11500","n11501","n11502"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"masculine of خَمْسَة (ḵamsa, “five”)","tags":["form-of","masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the five digits of the hand"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one fifth"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ḫamišum.\n\nFrom the root خ م س (ḵ m s); compare خَمْسَة (ḵamsa, “five”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11499","headword_ar":"خَمْسٌ","root":"xms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamosapN","text_ar":"خَمْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11500","headword_ar":"خُمْسٌ","root":"xms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xumusN","text_ar":"خُمُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11501","headword_ar":"خِمْسٌ","root":"xms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking of camels on the fifth day, counting the day of the next preceding drinking as the first; their drinking one day, then pasturing three days, then coming to the water on the fifth day, the first and last days, on which they drink, being thus reckoned"},{"kind":"text","text":": this is the correct explanation, accord. to Aboo-Sahl El-Khowlee; and Aboo-Zekereeyà says the like; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their pasturing three days, and coming to the water on the fourth day"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not counting the day of the next preceding watering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is evident that this explanation is virtually the same as that preceding]: (S, K:) accord. to Lth, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking of camels on the fourth day, counting the day on which they returned from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the next preceding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says, that this is a mistake; the day of returning from watering not being counted [when it is explained as meaning the drinking on the fourth day]: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomaAsN","text_ar":"اَخْمَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the only pl. form. (Sb, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zimo'N","text_ar":"ظِمْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaApN ximosN","text_ar":"فَلَاةٌ خِمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as in copies of the K, or it may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaApu ximosK","text_ar":"فَلَاةُ خِمْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A desert in which the water is far distant, so that the camels come to the water on the fourth day, exclusive of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next preceding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day on which they drank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K, TA.) Hence also the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaDoribu A^axomaAsFA liA^asodaAsK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَضْرِبُ اَخْمَاسًا لِاَسْدَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K *) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one makes a pretence of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxmAs","text_ar":"اخماس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fifth-day waterings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsdAs","text_ar":"اسداس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixth-day waterings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., he advances his camels from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximos","text_ar":"خِمْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidos","text_ar":"سِدْس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) a prov.: (TA:) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one strives to deceive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumvent"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) applied to him who acts towards another with artifice, pretending that he obeys him, or complies with his desire: (TA:) or to him who pretends one thing while he means another: (K:) and taken from the saying, related by AO and IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba A^axomaAsFA liA^asodaAsK","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ اَخْمَاسًا لِاَسْدَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a pretence of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxmAs","text_ar":"اخماس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsdAs","text_ar":"اسداس"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said of him who proposes a thing whereby he means another thing, which he commences and by slow degrees accomplishes: (TA:) for a man, when he desires to make a long journey, accustoms his camels to drink"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosFA sidosFA","text_ar":"خِمْسًا سِدْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the fifth day"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the sixth, in each case counting the day of the next preceding drinking as the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) the origin of the saying, accord. to IAar, being this: an old man was among his camels, accompanied by his sons, men, who pastured them, and who had been long far distant from their families; and he told them one day to pasture their camels"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboEFA","text_ar":"رِبْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. watering on the fourth day, counting the day of the next preceding watering as the first], which they did, proceeding in the way towards their families: then they proposed to do so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosFA","text_ar":"خِمْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidosFA","text_ar":"سِدْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": whereupon the old man, understanding what they meant, said, ye are doing nothing but making a pretence of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxmAs","text_ar":"اخماس"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the purpose of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsdAs","text_ar":"اسداس"},{"kind":"text","text":": the object of your desire is not the pasturing of them, but it is only your families. (TA.) [See below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xumusN","text_ar":"خُمُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying similar in words but different in meaning.] ―         -b2-  It is also used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoru ximosK","text_ar":"سَيْرُ خِمْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A journey in which the camels are watered only on the first and fifth days; a journey in which the second and third and fourth days are without water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jl*","text_ar":"جلذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximsN baSobaASN","text_ar":"خِمسٌ بَصْبَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaboSaAbN","text_ar":"صَبْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEoqaAEN","text_ar":"قَعْقَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HavoHaAvN","text_ar":"حَثْحَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSoHaASN","text_ar":"حَصْحَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A journey"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the camels are watered only on the first and fifth days,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the course of which, to the water, there is no flagging, by reason of its remoteness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) El-'Ajjáj uses the expression"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ximosN kaHaboli Al$~aEari AlmunoHat~i"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journey of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xms","text_ar":"خمس"},{"kind":"text","text":"without any deviation,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"made"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hair that has fallen off"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that is free from any unevenness. (L, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosN","text_ar":"خِمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fifth young one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) so called because first made for a king of El-Yemen named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosN","text_ar":"خِمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alximosu","text_ar":"الخِمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamiysN","text_ar":"خَمِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) For the latter word, we find in the work of Bkh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamiyS","text_ar":"خَمِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which, if correct, is masc. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamiySapN","text_ar":"خَمِيصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a small kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, and L.) [The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosN","text_ar":"خِمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodap","text_ar":"بُرْدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomaAsN","text_ar":"اَخْمَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxomuwsN","text_ar":"مَخْمُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","AA"]},{"entry_id":"n11502","headword_ar":"خُمُسٌ","root":"xms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xumosN","text_ar":"خُمْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fifth part;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamiysN","text_ar":"خَمِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":", and IAmb and Msb,) agreeably with a rule applicable in the case of every one of the units, except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valiyvN","text_ar":"ثَلِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) some allow this last; but AZ disallows it, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmys","text_ar":"خميس"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomaAsN","text_ar":"اَخْمَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba A^axomaAsahu fiY","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ اَخْمَاسَهُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaAsihi","text_ar":"اَسْدَاسِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned his five senses towards his six relative points;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely, above, below, before, behind, right, and left:] an allusion to the collecting all the thoughts to examine a thing, and turning the attention in all directions. (MF.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}